{"title":"Readers’ Rides: Patrick’s Niner RLT 9 Steel","link":"https://theradavist.com/2021/03/readers-rides-patricks-niner-rlt-9-steel/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=readers-rides-patricks-niner-rlt-9-steel","date":1615571542000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/officialdurkin/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Pat Cummins</a> is a big sweetheart. The ex-MMA fighter is a lover of singlespeeds and mountains. I shot <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2019/08/outside-online-pat-cummins-is-a-ufc-fighter-that-rides-a-rigid-mtb/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">some photos for Outside Magazine</a> of him a few years back on his Niner singlespeed but his recent acquisition has some extra gears. Read on below for some photos of this new build by <a href=\"https://teamdreambicyclingteam.com/pages/the-cub-house\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">the Cub House</a>, with words by Danny from the Cub House.<span id=\"more-206907\"></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206909\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-2-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t know Patrick Cummins he is probably the most intimidating looking nicest guy you will ever meet. If you do know him then you know he shreds on his single speed MTB. When he came to the shop with this Niner frame in a box he had some rad ideas, and that is the most fun part about building up bikes. </p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1334\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-8-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206914\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-8-of-14.jpg?w=1334&amp;quality=75 1334w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-8-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,1535&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-8-of-14.jpg?resize=768,1151&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-8-of-14.jpg?resize=700,1049&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-8-of-14.jpg?resize=1025,1536&amp;quality=75 1025w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1334px) 100vw, 1334px\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206910\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-3-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>Taking what someone has in their head and working together to make it happen. He had a pretty simple but clear vision in mind, as we chatted through the gate at the Cub House (this build was started when we had the shop set up for outdoors only). He said “I want some gold, I want some bourbon Chris King stuff and I want my Niner to be super fun” and we went from there. Which brings up another point. </p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206916\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-9-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206920\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-13-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to get lost in the fancy parts we all know and love when doing custom builds, I know I was. Patrick wanted a gold stem and seat post to accent the bourgon Chris King parts. I got stuck trying to think of what cockpit parts to use, or what we could do for some custom anodization until he emailed a photo of a Promax stem, and look at the result. It&#8217;s awesome. It might not be a $300 stem and ultra fancy seatpost but the impact they have are great. </p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206918\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-11-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206915\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-7-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206912\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-5-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206913\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-6-of-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>Overall even though it took a little while to hunt down all the parts the whole build</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1334\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-4-of-14.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206911\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-4-of-14.jpg?w=1334&amp;quality=75 1334w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-4-of-14.jpg?resize=1024,1535&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-4-of-14.jpg?resize=768,1151&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-4-of-14.jpg?resize=700,1049&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/Durkin-Niner-4-of-14.jpg?resize=1025,1536&amp;quality=75 1025w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1334px) 100vw, 1334px\" /></p>\n<p>Build List:<br />\n-Niner RLT 9 Steel<br />\n-Shimano GRX Drivetrain<br />\n-Chris King Matte Bourgon R45’s to White Industries G25A 650 Rims (built at the shop by Simon)<br />\n-Ultradynamico Rose Tires<br />\n-Praxis Zayante Carbon Crank<br />\n-Selle Anatomica Saddle<br />\n-Chris King Matte Bourbon Headset<br />\n-Promax Stem/Seatpost w/White Industries Headset spacers that matched!<br />\n-Zipp Service Course XPLR Bars<br />\n-KMC X11 SL Gold Chain</p>","author":"prolly","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"627d10b5f14af24e78a158b31fdd992748328a5d992cef456886ce4c7b558d19","category":"Cycling"}